summary: TL* THE CONTACT OWNS A 2008 FORD RANGER. WHILE DRIVING 65 MPH OVER BLACK ICE, THE CONTACT LOST CONTROL OF THE VEHICLE UNDER AN OVERPASS. AS A RESULT, THE VEHICLE FLIPPED OVER AND LANDED ON ITS PASSENGER SIDE. THE AIR BAGS DID NOT DEPLOY. A POLICE REPORT WAS FILED AND THERE WERE NO INJURIES SUSTAINED. THE VEHICLE WAS TOWED TO THE CONTACT'S RESIDENCE. THE DEALER AND MANUFACTURER WERE NOT NOTIFIED. THE FAILURE MILEAGE WAS 133,000.
